@Steve L 

Come on, Steve, you know I know it's a word, and you know from my comment I'm defending its use and not questioning its legitimacy. While it may "sidestep any racial discomfort" for you or me, we can't claim to know how such a (mildly) freighted word might sit with anyone else. I'm only saying that this word has a little more than usual freightedness, and that there's a slightly higher than usual risk in its deployment in a puzzle that someone -- rationally or not, since such words trigger an emotional response -- will object to it. That's what makes its use here a little daring. 

But since most of the top recommended comments object to this puzzle's difficulty and/or lack of excitement, I guess the nattering nabobs are focusing on other issues, not racial ones. So I guess it didn't trigger anyone after all. I'm glad.

@Andrew 

I didn't get that feeling at all, so I'd be curious to get some examples of things you didn't care about.

